HEADWORD: endogenic
<hw>en`do*gen"ic</hw></mhw>
<pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Relating to or
arising from an internal process; same as <er>endogenous</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Relating to the interior of the
earth; of or pertaining to a metamorphic process occurring within a
planet. Opposed to <contr>exogenetic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> endogenic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endogenous</ent>⟦br⟧
